fields.value: Replication data for: Legislative Voting Project

dsDescriptionValue.value:
This project involves the collection of recorded votes from 21 legislative chambers in 19 countries, as well as interviews with 55 legislators and political party leaders in 8 countries.  The data are analyzed in various articles, as well as the book Legislative Voting
& Accountability.

publicationCitation.value: Carey, John M. 2007. Legislative Voting Project. Carey data archive. www.dartmouth.edu/~jcarey. project available here
Carey, John M. 2007. Legislative Voting Project. Carey data archive. www.dartmouth.edu/~jcarey. project available here

Legislative Voting and Accountability. Book manuscript (January 2008 draft) forthcoming from Cambridge University Press. manuscript available here

“Competing principals, political institutions, and party unity in legislative voting.” American Journal of Political Science 51(1):92-107. January 2007. article available here

“Parties and Accountable Government in New Democracies.” Co-authored with Andrew Reynolds. Party Politics 13(2):255-274. January 2007. article available here

“Recorded voting and accountability in the United States and Latin American Legislatures.” Timothy Power and Nicol Rae, eds., Exporting Congress? The influence of the U.S. Congress on world legislatures. University of Pittsburgh Press. 2007. book available here

“Legislative Organization.” Sarah Binder, Rod Rhodes, and Bert Rockman, eds., The Oxford Handbook of Political Institutions. Oxford: Oxford University Press. 2006: 431-454. book available here
